comments:
There are two problems and both of them are related to SWT.MeasureItem. I have waited a long time for this enhancement. And I wish you guys can fix it as soon as possible.


Firstly when I have used this code:

	table = new Table(this, SWT.VIRTUAL | SWT.FULL_SELECTION | SWT.BORDER | SWT.CHECK);
	table.setLayoutData(new GridData(GridData.FILL, GridData.FILL, true, true));
	table.setLinesVisible(true);
	table.setHeaderVisible(true);

	table.addListener(SWT.MeasureItem, new Listener() {
			public void handleEvent(Event e) {

				e.height = 20;
			}
		});
 And change the first row background color to yellow. Let?s look at the Table cell [0,0], it fills part of background color only.



Secondly when you select on a row and then move your mouse cursor within the selected row. Let?s look at the Table cell [0,0] again, part of the table cell line is disappeared.

Actually there is one more problem. When I was going to create a customized selection color buy using the swt.painitem, after that just select a row and moving your mouse within the selected row. You will find that the table cell [0,0] always repaint itself. Sometime it makes the text disappear.

1) SN, a full snippet that shows the first problem follows.  The background colour does not extend to the right bound of the cell.

public static void main(String[] args) {
	final Display display = new Display();
	Shell shell = new Shell(display);
	shell.setLayout(new GridLayout());
	shell.setBounds(10, 10, 200, 200);
	Table table = new Table(shell, SWT.CHECK);
	table.setBounds(10,10,100,100);
	table.setLinesVisible(true);
	for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
		new TableItem(table, SWT.NONE).setText("item " + i);
	}
	table.addListener(SWT.MeasureItem, new Listener() {
		public void handleEvent(Event e) {
			e.height = 20;
		}
	});
	table.getItem(0).setBackground(display.getSystemColor(SWT.COLOR_RED));
	shell.open();
	while (!shell.isDisposed()) {
		if (!display.readAndDispatch()) display.sleep();
	}
	display.dispose();
}

2) I've logged new bug 150990 to track the second problem, since it's easier if each bug report deals with one specific problem.

3) The third problem is known and I'm sure is logged in another open bug report, but I can't find it at the moment.
